{"questionId":"3590664","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The probability that at least <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math> patients will be cured is less than <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>30</mn><mo>%</mo></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the least value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to write an expression containing <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math> inside the brackets of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>(</mo><mo> </mo><mo>)</mo></math> <strong>AND</strong></p>\n<p>including <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>X</mi><mo>≥</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn></math>&nbsp; <strong>OR</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>X</mi><mo>≤</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn></math> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> (A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>98</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>using binomcdf in GDC for at least two different values of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math> greater than <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>90</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>X</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>97</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>696683</mn><mo>…</mo></math>&nbsp; <strong>AND</strong>&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>X</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>98</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>778249</mn><mo>…</mo></math> (seen)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>X</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>97</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>303316</mn><mo>…</mo></math>&nbsp; <strong>AND</strong>&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>X</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>98</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>221750</mn><mo>…</mo></math> (seen)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>98</mn></math> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"3590664","referenceCode":"23M.2.SL.TZ2.4d","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the least value of n.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.8—Binomial distribution"],"memb